about.description:
The pyparsing module is an alternative approach to creating and executing
simple grammars, vs. the traditional lex/yacc approach, or the use of
regular expressions. The pyparsing module provides a library of classes
that client code uses to construct the grammar directly in Python code.

name: pyparsing
raw_recipe:
{% set version="2.1.7" %}

package:
  name: pyparsing
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: pyparsing-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/p/pyparsing/pyparsing-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7faf33a14ab1413d9a73ffe4b5a02d604cff6fba2bc39d5ea71b10ffc67d75ac

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - pyparsing

about:
  home: http://pyparsing.wikispaces.com/
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Create and execute simple grammars
  description: |
    The pyparsing module is an alternative approach to creating and executing
    simple grammars, vs. the traditional lex/yacc approach, or the use of
    regular expressions. The pyparsing module provides a library of classes
    that client code uses to construct the grammar directly in Python code.
  doc_url: http://pyparsing.wikispaces.com/Documentation
  dev_url: https://svn.code.sf.net/p/pyparsing/code/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - msarahan
